name: Chicken Adobo Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green peas'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'carrots'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked rice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'chicken adobo'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'white pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions'}
steps: Pour oil into a large, nonstick skillet over medium heat. When oil is hot, add onions and stir about 1 minute. Add garlic and stir about 30 seconds.. Stir in frozen green peas and matchstick carrots and cook, stirring, 3 to 4 minutes. Add rice and stir in sesame oil and soy sauce. Cook, stirring, about 2 minutes.. Stir in chicken, using a lifting motion, to make sure all the rice is coated with any sauce from the chicken adobo. Cook and stir about 2 minutes. Season with salt and white pepper.. Move the skillet contents to one side of the skillet and pour in beaten egg. Allow egg to spread into a thin layer. When egg is set, score into strips, then stir into rice mixture. Remove from heat. Sprinkle on chopped scallions and serve warm.

name: Hot Dog Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'peanut oil'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': None, 'name': 'hot dogs, sliced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked rice'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'frozen mixed vegetables'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'rice vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce, plus more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'riracha'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions, thinly sliced'}
steps: Heat oil over high in a large deep skillet or wok. Add onions and cook until lightly browned and softened, about 2 minutes. Add hot dogs and cook, stirring constantly until browned. Add in rice and sesame oil and cook, stirring constantly, about 1 minute. Stir in ginger, garlic, salt and pepper.. Spread mixture into an even layer and cook, undisturbed, until rice is lightly toasted, about 2 minutes. Add in mixed vegetables and stir, then cook undisturbed for 2 minutes. Push rice mixture to the sides and create a space in the center of the skillet. Add butter to the skillet and allow to melt. Crack in eggs and cook, stirring only the eggs until they are soft scrambled. Fold eggs into rice mixture and stir until evenly mixed. Stir in vinegar and soy sauce and cook for 1 minute. Remove from heat.. Combine mayo, Sriracha and lemon juice in a small bowl. Serve fried rice topped with a drizzle of mayo mixture and sprinkle with green onions.

name: Easy Chicken Fried Rice

steps: Heat canola and sesame oils in a large, nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add carrot and 1/4 cup green onion; cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Stir in garlic powder and ginger and cook for 2 minutes. Stir in rice, salt, and pepper; cook, stirring only once or twice, until rice is lightly browned, about 4 to 5 minutes. Stir in chicken and peas; cook for 2 minutes.. Push rice mixture to the sides of the pan, creating a circle in the middle. Add butter to the center of the pan. When melted, pour eggs into the center. Cook eggs, stirring often, until almost set, about 3 minutes. Stir eggs into the rice mixture. Stir in soy sauce and rice vinegar; cook for 2 more minutes.. Serve immediately topped with Sriracha mayo and green onions.

name: Winter Vegetable Fried Rice

steps: Spray a wok or deep skillet with cooking spray and preheat over medium-high heat.. Whisk eggs and water in a bowl until well mixed. Scramble eggs in wok until no longer runny, but still moist, about 1 minute. Remove from wok or skillet; set aside.. Wipe out the wok and return to medium-high heat. Add oil and garlic. Cook garlic until fragrant, about 30 seconds, stirring frequently. Add cabbage, carrots, snow peas, onions, and sprouts . Cook for 2 minutes, stirring frequently to mix ingredients. Add rice, egg, green onion, soy sauce, and chili sauce. and cook until heated through, 3 to 4 minutes, stirring frequently.

name: Cabbage Fried Rice

Cook and stir eggs in the hot oil until scrambled and set, 3 to 4 minutes. Transfer eggs to a plate, clean the pan, and return to medium high heat.. name: Air Fryer Shrimp Fried Rice

name: Leftover Turkey Fried Rice

name: Air Fryer Fried Rice

steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat a 5-quart air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) according to the manufacturer's instructions.. name: Island-Style Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'uncooked jasmine rice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'canola oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) can', 'name': 'fully cooked luncheon meat (such as SPAM), cubed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced Chinese sweet pork sausage (lup cheong)'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'canola oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) can', 'name': 'pineapple chunks, drained'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'oyster sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped green onion'}
steps: Bring water and rice to a boil in a saucepan over high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until rice is tender and liquid has been absorbed, 20 to 25 minutes. Let rice cool completely.. Heat 2 teaspoons oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Cook and stir luncheon meat and sausage in hot oil until browned. Remove meat mixture to a plate. Pour beaten eggs into the same skillet; cook and stir until eggs are scrambled. Transfer eggs to the plate with meat mixture.. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in the same skillet over medium heat. Cook and stir cooled rice in hot oil until heated through and beginning to brown, about 2 minutes. Add garlic powder; toss rice to develop garlic taste, about 1 minute. Stir in cooked meats, scrambled eggs, pineapple, and oyster sauce. Cook and stir until well combined and heated through, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in green onion to serve.

name: Crab Fried Rice

name: Tsao Mi Fun (Taiwanese Fried Rice Noodles)
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'thinly sliced pork loin'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rice wine'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Chinese five-spice powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'dried Chinese black mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'dried rice vermicelli'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dried small shrimp'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrots, cut into matchstick strips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'bean sprouts'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'leaves', 'name': 'napa cabbage, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'sprigs', 'name': 'fresh cilantro for garnish'}
steps: Place the pork into a mixing bowl and pour in the soy sauce and rice wine. Sprinkle with the white pepper, five-spice powder, and cornstarch. Mix well, then set aside to marinate. Soak the mushrooms in a bowl of cold water for 20 minutes, then pour off the water, cut off and discard the stems of the mushrooms. Slice the mushrooms thinly and reserve. Soak the rice vermicelli in a separate bowl of cold water for 10 minutes, then pour off the water and set the noodles aside.. Heat 1 tablespoon of the vegetable oil in a wok or large skillet over medium heat. Pour in the eggs, and cook until firm, flipping once, to make a pancake. Remove the egg pancake, and allow to cool, then thinly slice and place into a large bowl. Heat 2 more tablespoons of the vegetable oil in the wok over high heat. Stir in the garlic and dried shrimp, and cook until the shrimp become aromatic, about 20 seconds. Next, add the pork along with the marinade, and cook until the pork is no longer pink, about 4 minutes. Stir in the carrots and onion, and cook until the carrots begin to soften, about 3 minutes. Finally, add the bean sprouts, napa cabbage, and sliced mushrooms; cook and stir until the vegetables are tender, about 3 minutes more. Scrape the pork mixture into the bowl along with the eggs, then wipe out the wok and return it to the stove over medium-high heat.. Heat the remaining vegetable oil in the wok, then stir in the drained rice vermicelli noodles. Cook and stir for a few minutes until the noodles soften, then stir in the reserved pork mixture. Scrape the mixture in to a serving bowl and garnish with cilantro to serve.

name: Egg Fried Rice

steps: Heat a wok or large skillet over high heat; add 1 teaspoon canola oil. Cook and stir eggs in the hot oil until scrambled and set, 3 to 4 minutes. Transfer eggs to a plate, clean the wok, and return to high heat.. Mix 1 tablespoon canola oil, carrots, and salt in the hot wok; cook and stir for 2 minutes. Add garlic to carrots; cook and stir until garlic is fragrant and browned, about 2 minutes. Stir peas and scallions into carrot mixture; cook and stir until peas are warmed, 1 to 2 minutes. Lower heat to medium.. Stir rice into carrot mixture; add scrambled eggs, soy sauce, salt, and pepper. Cook and stir rice mixture until heated through, 2 to 3 minutes.

name: Garlic Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'uncooked white rice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'onion, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}

Melt the butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic; cook and stir until fragrant and lightly browned. Stir in rice and cook until coated and heated through. Remove from the heat and stir in the lemon juice.

name: Fried Rice with Ginger, Hoisin, and Sesame
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'uncooked white rice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'hoisin sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'barbeque sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'grated fresh ginger root'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated carrot'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'frozen pea pods'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'frozen chopped broccoli, thawed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sesame seeds, lightly toasted'}
steps: Melt the butter in a small saucepan over medium heat. Add the uncooked rice, and cook until toasted, stirring occasionally. Pour in the water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover, and cook for about 15 minutes, or until tender.. While the rice is cooking, mix together the hoisin sauce, barbeque sauce, peanut butter, soy sauce, garlic, and ginger. Set aside.. When the rice is done cooking, heat the sesame oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat. When it begins to smoke, add the onion and fry until clear. Add the carrot, and cook for about 1 minute, then add the rice, and stir fry for about 2 minutes. Add the broccoli and peas; cook and stir for about 1 minute. Push everything to the sides of the wok, and crack the eggs into the center. Scramble until cooked through, trying to keep the raw egg from mixing with everything else. When the eggs are cooked, stir them in with the rice.. Turn off the heat, and stir in about half of the sauce, tasting and adding more as desired. You may not need all of the sauce, but if you serve this with a meat it makes a good sauce for that too. Sprinkle with sesame seeds before serving.

name: Easy Pineapple Fried Rice

name: House Fried Rice

name: Thai Fried Rice with Pineapple and Chicken
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon, diced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'shallots, sliced'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'chicken breast, cut into small cubes'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'curry powder, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil, or as needed (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg yolks, beaten'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked jasmine rice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red Thai bird chile pepper, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'whole cilantro leaves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'fish sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'tiger prawns, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh pineapple'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green onions, finely chopped'}
steps: Place bacon in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat; cook and stir until crisp, about 10 minutes. Remove bacon with a slotted spoon onto a paper towel-lined plate; set aside. Reserve bacon drippings in the wok.. Cook and stir shallots in bacon drippings over medium-high heat until fragrant and light brown, 1 to 2 minutes.. Stir chicken into shallots and cook, without stirring, until browned on one side, 45 seconds to 1 minute; stir. Continue cooking until chicken is browned, about 1 minute. Mix chile pepper, cilantro, soy sauce, remaining 2 teaspoons curry powder, fish sauce, and sugar into rice mixture; add shrimp and cook until shrimp is cooked through and pink, about 2 minutes. Fold pineapple, green onions, and bacon into rice mixture.

name: Japanese Shrimp Fried Rice with Yum Yum Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'uncooked jasmine rice'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'sweet onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, crushed and minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen peas and carrots'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'oyster sauce'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lemon, juiced, divided'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'uncooked medium shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ginger paste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}
steps: Bring 3 cups water and rice to a boil in a saucepan. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until rice is tender and water has been absorbed, 20 to 25 minutes. Set aside and let cool.. Heat 2 tablespoons vegetable oil in a large, deep skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook until soft and translucent, about 5 minutes. Lift the edges to allow any uncooked egg to flow onto the hot pan, about 1 minute. Flip omelet in one piece and cook until fully set, about 30 seconds. name: Steak Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 pound)', 'name': 'flank steak'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'white sugar, divided'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'kosher salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'grated ginger'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'frozen peas, thawed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked white rice'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sesame oil'}
steps: Pat flank steak dry with a paper towel. Cut into bite-sized pieces and transfer to a medium bowl. Season with 1 teaspoon sugar, salt, and pepper. Add cornstarch and toss until well coated.. Heat 1 teaspoon oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat. Add eggs and scramble using a rubber spatula, 3 to 5 minutes. Remove eggs to a dish.. Add 1 teaspoon oil and 1/2 of the meat to the wok. Increase heat to high and cook until browned on all sides and cooked through, 3 to 5 minutes. Remove to a plate. name: Curry Pineapple Fried Rice

name: Ground Beef Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'carrots, chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'green bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'sweet onion (such as Vidalia®), chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cooked rice, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}

name: Vegetarian Thai Curry Fried Rice

steps: Rinse rice a few times under cold running water until water runs clear.. Bring rice, water, and coconut water to a boil in a saucepan. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until rice is tender and water has been absorbed, 20 to 25 minutes.. Heat oil in a wok or large cast iron skillet over medium heat. name: Chicken Fried Rice Recipes That Rival Takeout
Chinese Stir-Fried Sticky Rice with Chinese Sausage
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'glutinous rice'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried shrimp'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'dried scallops'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '', 'name': 'dried shiitake mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'links', 'name': 'Chinese sausage, diced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'hot water, or more as needed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'light soy sauce, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'dark soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro, or to taste'}
steps: Soak rice in a large bowl of water until mostly translucent, about 4 hours. Rinse and drain thoroughly.. When the rice is almost finished soaking, soak shrimp, scallops, and mushrooms in three separate bowls of water until softened, about 15 minutes. Drain shrimp and scallops. Drain mushrooms and reserve mushroom water. Chop shrimp, scallops, and mushrooms into small pieces.. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Pour in eggs and swirl the skillet to spread into a thin layer. Cook until mostly firm, about 1 minute. Flip and cook until no longer runny, 3 to 5 minutes.. Add hot water, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring until water is absorbed between each addition. Cook until rice is softened, about 25 minutes.. Season rice with both soy sauces and sugar. Stir in egg ribbons and sausage mixture. Top with cilantro before serving.

name: Fried Rice

name: Spam Fried Rice

name: Thai Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon, sliced crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'tomato, cubed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh pineapple'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked jasmine rice, cooled'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ketchup'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'light soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly ground white pepper'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cucumber, sliced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green onions, chopped'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lime, cut into wedges'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green Thai chile peppers'}
steps: Heat a large skillet or wok over medium heat and cook bacon until browned and crisp, about 5 minutes. Drain, reserving bacon grease in a bowl. Spoon 2 tablespoons grease back into the skillet.. Increase heat to medium-high and cook garlic until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add onion and cook, stirring often, until softened, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in tomato and pineapple and stir-fry until warmed through, about 2 minutes.. Increase heat to high and add 1 tablespoon bacon grease. Add rice and stir-fry, breaking up with a spatula so it gets coated well with bacon grease. Cook for about 3 minutes. Season with ketchup, soy sauce, sugar, and white pepper.. Move rice mixture to one side of the skillet or wok and pour beaten eggs onto the empty side. Stir-fry until eggs are almost set, 2 to 3 minutes. Mix eggs with rice mixture. Fold in bacon bits. Serve with cucumber, green onions, cilantro, lemon wedges, and chile peppers.

name: Pineapple Shrimp Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'coconut oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'carrot, diced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'uncooked medium shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced ham'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked jasmine rice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'diced pineapple'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'tomato, diced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green onions, thinly sliced'}
steps: Melt coconut oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Add onion, carrot, and garlic; stir-fry until tender, about 3 minutes. Add shrimp and ham; stir-fry until shrimp are almost cooked through, about 2 minutes. Add cooked rice and soy sauce; continue to cook and stir for 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.. Stir pineapple, tomato, and green onions into fried rice until thoroughly combined.

name: Thai Shrimp Fried Rice (Kao Pad Goong)
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'oyster sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fish sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'canola oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'uncooked medium shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped green onions, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'minced garlic, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen mixed vegetables'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'day-old cooked white rice'}
steps: Stir together oyster sauce, fish sauce, soy sauce, and brown sugar in a small bowl. Set aside.. Heat 1/2 tablespoon oil in a large cast iron skillet or wok over medium heat. Add shrimp, 1/4 cup green onions, and 1 tablespoon garlic. Cook, stirring constantly, until shrimp are firm and opaque, 3 to 4 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.. Without cleaning the skillet, add another 1/2 tablespoon oil over medium heat. Add remaining 1/4 cup green onions, remaining 1 tablespoon garlic, and mixed vegetables. Cook, stirring often, until vegetables are tender, about 4 minutes. Push to the side of the skillet and add another 1 tablespoon oil to the center. Add beaten egg and let sit for 20 seconds; then stir gently until large curds form, about 1 minute. Stir cooked eggs and vegetables together.. Increase heat to medium-high and add remaining 1 tablespoon oil. Stir in cooked rice and reserved sauce; flatten rice in skillet. Cook, flipping and turning occasionally, until rice is brown and crispy in some spots, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in cooked shrimp.

name: Kimchi Fried Rice

name: Shrimp Fried Rice I
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'uncooked white rice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'celery, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'cooked salad shrimp'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrots, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, diced'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'snow peas, trimmed and halved'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}
steps: In a medium saucepan bring water to a boil. Add the white rice. Return to a boil, reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 20 minutes, or until rice is tender.. In a small skillet scramble the eggs in a small amount of sesame oil. Remove from heat once scrambled.. In a large skillet, brown onion and celery in remaining sesame oil. Add shrimp and carrots, onion, celery, red pepper, pea pods, and green pepper. Add white rice and stir well. Add soy sauce (if desired) and eggs, stir thoroughly until heated through.

name: Thai Beef Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'drops', 'name': 'sesame oil, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'finely chopped green onion (white and light green parts)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'cooked and crumbled ground beef'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced fresh tomato'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fish sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked jasmine rice'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'wedges', 'name': 'lime (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}
steps: Warm vegetable oil and sesame oil in a wok or large skillet. Add bell pepper, onion, and green onion; cook for 2 minutes. Add ground beef, sprinkle garlic powder over mixture, and cook for 1 minute longer.. Stir in diced tomato, fish sauce, and soy sauce; saute for 2 minutes. Add rice, mix until combined, and cook until heated through, 7 to 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper and squeeze lime wedged over top.. Pour beaten egg into a separate, small pan and let cook for 30 seconds. Lift the edges of the omelet so that any uncooked egg runs under the cooked edges and comes into contact with the hot skillet. Shake and tilt the skillet to move the uncooked egg. Repeat until the top is set, about 4 minutes.. Divide rice into two portions and serve 1/2 of the omelet over each serving.

name: Pineapple Fried Rice II
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'uncooked white rice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green onions, thinly sliced including tops'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced ham'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peas'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) can', 'name': 'pineapple chunks, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}
steps: Bring the rice and water to a boil in a saucepan over high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until the rice is tender, and the liquid has been absorbed, 20 to 25 minutes. Spread cooked rice out on a rimmed baking sheet and refrigerate until cooled, about 20 minutes.. Heat sesame oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Cook and stir the green onions, ham, and peas in the hot oil until onions have softened, about 2 minutes. Stir the pineapple chunks into the wok; cook until pineapple begins to darken, about 2 minute. Push ingredients to the side of the wok, and pour beaten egg in the center. Cook until egg begins to set, about 30 seconds. Stir together all contents of the wok.. Mix the cooled rice, sugar, salt, white pepper, and garlic powder into the wok; stir constantly to keep from sticking. Cook until heated through, about 3 minutes. Sprinkle the rice with the soy sauce, and stir to combine.

name: Sheet Pan Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced onion'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced carrot'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'canola oil'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked and cooled rice'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'frozen peas'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'green onions, chopped'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Sriracha'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'rice vinegar'}
steps: Set an oven rack in the center of the oven and preheat the oven's broiler.. Make the fried rice: Toss onion and carrot with oil on a rimmed baking sheet until coated; arrange in a single layer.. Broil in the preheated oven for 5 minutes.. Add rice, salt, and pepper to the sheet pan and toss to coat. Continue to broil until rice is just golden, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring halfway through.. Add frozen peas, garlic, and soy sauce; toss to evenly coat and spread in an even layer. Use the back of a spoon to form four indentations in the rice mixture. Crack an egg into each indentation. Broil until egg whites are set, about 3 minutes.. Meanwhile, make the Sriracha mayo: Stir mayonnaise, Sriracha, and rice vinegar together in a small bowl until well combined.. Drizzle Sriracha mayo over fried rice and sprinkle with green onions.

name: Glo's Sausage Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground pork sausage'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'head', 'name': 'cabbage, cored and shredded'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrots, chopped'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked white rice, cold'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'bean sprouts, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen green peas, thawed'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green onions, chopped'}
steps: In a skillet over medium-high heat, cook the sausage until evenly browned. Drain, and remove sausage from the pan. In the same pan, using the remaining coating of grease from the sausage, scramble the eggs, stirring frequently until cooked through. Set aside.. Heat the oil in a very large skillet or electric skillet over medium-high heat. Stir fry the cabbage and carrots just until the cabbage has wilted. Add the cold rice, and fry, stirring so that there are no clumps. Mix in the sausage and pour in some soy sauce. Stir in bean sprouts, peas, and eggs, mixing well so there are no big chunks of egg. Season with pepper, and stir in green onions just before removing from the heat. Adjust soy sauce to taste, and serve.

name: Instant Pot Chicken Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg, separated, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'rice vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breast, cubed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'long-grain brown rice'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'peanut oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced fresh mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green onions, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'low-sodium vegetable broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen peas and carrots'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'fresh snow peas'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced water chestnuts, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh broccoli'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground white pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh bean sprouts'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce, or more to taste'}
steps: Whisk egg white in a large bowl. Whisk in cornstarch and rice vinegar. Add chicken and stir until completely coated. Allow to sit for 10 minutes, then remove chicken and pat dry with a paper towel.. Meanwhile, rinse rice under cool running water until water runs clear. Set aside to drain.. Turn on a multi-functional pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot) and select Saute function. Add peanut oil and chicken; saute for 2 to 3 minutes. Add mushrooms, green onions, and garlic; saute until fragrant and mushrooms have softened, 6 to 7 minutes. Turn off Saute function.. Add vegetable broth, rice, frozen peas and carrots, snow peas, water chestnuts, and broccoli. Stir in pepper. Select Rice function and close and lock the lid. Set timer for 15 minutes.. Release pressure using the natural-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, for 8 minutes. Release any remaining pressure carefully using the quick-release method according to manufacturer's instructions. Unlock and remove the lid.. Fluff rice with a rice spatula, add sesame oil, and turn on Saute function. Whisk together remaining egg yolk and 2 eggs in a small bowl and stir into rice mixture, working slowly and in a circular fashion until eggs are distributed throughout the rice and are fully cooked, 3 to 5 minutes. Turn off Saute function and fold in bean sprouts and soy sauce. Serve immediately.

name: Thai-Inspired Beef Fried Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'shallot, chopped'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'fresh bird’s eye chiles, minced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked jasmine rice, cooled'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fish sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'oyster sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped sweet Thai basil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'wedges', 'name': 'lime'}
steps: Heat a wok or skillet over medium-high heat. Add vegetable oil and cook shallot and minced chiles until translucent and fragrant, 3 to 5 minutes. Add garlic and stir-fry until fragrant, about 1 minute. Mix in ground beef and cook, stirring often, until evenly browned, about 5 minutes. Use a slotted spoon to transfer the beef mixture to a plate.. Reduce heat to medium and stir in rice, breaking up any lumps. Allow rice to cook, folding it constantly to soak up the juices from the wok, about 10 minutes. Make a well in the middle of the rice and add beaten eggs. Swirl the eggs and rice together with small circular motions until all the rice is coated with eggs.. Return the beef mixture to the wok and toss to combine. Drizzle with soy sauce, fish sauce, and oyster sauce while tossing to mix. Cook for another few minutes until well combined. Remove from heat. Fold in cilantro and basil.. Distribute between 2 bowls and squeeze 1 lime wedge on each serving.

name: Fried Rice with Tofu
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'tofu'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce, divided, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrot, peeled and finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked rice, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'tomato, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'ground white pepper to taste'}
steps: Combine tofu and 2 tablespoons soy sauce in a bowl and marinate while you prepare the rest of the ingredients.. Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add onions and carrot; cook until lightly browned, about 5 minutes. Add tofu and marinade and cook for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in rice and cook for 3 minutes while stirring.. Move all ingredients to one half of the skillet and crack eggs into the empty half. Cook for 2 minutes until eggs start to set. Mix eggs and the rest of the ingredients until well combined. Season with remaining soy sauce and sugar; mix well.. Stir tomato into the skillet; cook and mix for 1 minute. Season with salt, white pepper, and more soy sauce if desired.
